

Manage Kubernetes Resources using CLI (kubectl + Minikube)

I’ve cleaned everything so you can run smoothly and get output without confusion.

✅ 🔹 OVERVIEW (What you are doing)
You will:

Install tools
Start a local Kubernetes cluster
Create a Pod
Create & scale a Deployment
Expose it as a Service
Access it in browser
Clean everything
🔹 Step 0: Prerequisites
Install:

Docker Desktop
kubectl
Minikube
👉 Start Docker before continuing

🔹 Step 1: Verify Installations
docker --version
kubectl version --client
minikube version
✔ If versions appear → OK

🔹 Step 2: Start Kubernetes Cluster
minikube start --driver=docker
🔹 Step 3: Check Cluster
minikube status
kubectl get nodes
✅ Output should show:

Ready
🔹 Step 4: Create Pod YAML File
Create file:

nginx-pod.yaml
Paste:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx-pod
  labels:
    app: nginx
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:latest
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
🔹 Step 5: Create Pod
kubectl apply -f nginx-pod.yaml
🔹 Step 6: Check Pod
kubectl get pods
✅ Expected:

nginx-pod   1/1   Running
🔹 Step 7: View Pod Details
kubectl describe pod nginx-pod
🔹 Step 8: Access Pod in Browser
kubectl port-forward pod/nginx-pod 8080:80
👉 Open:

http://localhost:8080
✅ You will see Nginx Welcome Page

🔹 Step 9: Delete Pod
kubectl delete pod nginx-pod
🔹 Step 10: Create Deployment
kubectl create deployment my-nginx --image=nginx
🔹 Step 11: Check Deployment
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods
🔹 Step 12: Scale Deployment
kubectl scale deployment my-nginx --replicas=3
🔹 Step 13: Verify Scaling
kubectl get pods
✅ You should see 3 pods

🔹 Step 14: Update Image (Rolling Update)
kubectl set image deployment/my-nginx nginx=nginx:1.25
Check status:

kubectl rollout status deployment/my-nginx
🔹 Step 15: Rollback (if needed)
kubectl rollout undo deployment/my-nginx
🔹 Step 16: Expose Deployment as Service
kubectl expose deployment my-nginx --type=NodePort --port=80
🔹 Step 17: Check Service
kubectl get svc
🔹 Step 18: Get URL
minikube service my-nginx --url
👉 Open the URL in browser

✅ You will see Nginx page again

🔹 Step 19: Delete Service
kubectl delete svc my-nginx
🔹 Step 20: Cleanup
kubectl delete deployment my-nginx
kubectl delete all --all -n default
🔹 Step 21: Stop Cluster
minikube stop
(Optional delete cluster)

minikube delete
🔥 Common Errors (VERY IMPORTANT)
❌ Minikube not starting
✔ Run:

minikube start --driver=docker
❌ Pod stuck in Pending
✔ Check:

kubectl describe pod nginx-pod
❌ Port already in use
✔ Change:

8081:80
❌ No browser output
✔ Run again:

minikube service my-nginx --url
🧠 Viva Short Answers
👉 What is Kubernetes?
Container orchestration platform.

👉 What is Pod?
Smallest unit in Kubernetes (runs container).

👉 What is Deployment?
Manages multiple pods and scaling.

👉 What is Service?
Exposes application to network.

👉 What is Minikube?
Runs local Kubernetes cluster.

👉 What is kubectl?
Command-line tool to manage Kubernetes.

✅ Final Memory Trick
👉 Start → Pod → Deployment → Scale → Service → Access → Cleanup

